"title": "5964: temper",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "5964",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>A person's usual character or temporary frame of mind. The term often refers to a temporary state of anger, which Scripture insists must be brief and controlled.</p>\n<h2>General references to good temper</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov16:32\">PRO 16:32</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov15:1\">PRO 15:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt5:39\">MAT 5:39</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph4:2\">EPH 4:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim3:2-1Tim3:3\">1TI 3:2–3:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim2:24\">2TI 2:24</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas3:17\">JAS 3:17</a></p>\n<h2>People who kept their temper under provocation</h2>\n<h3>Joseph</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen50:15-Gen50:21\">GEN 50:15–50:21</a></p>\n<h3>David</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam16:5-2Sam16:13\">2SA 16:5–16:13</a></p>\n<h3>Jesus Christ</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke23:33-Luke23:34\">LUK 23:33–23:34</a></p>\n<h3>Stephen</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts7:59-Acts7:60\">ACT 7:59–7:60</a></p>\n<h2>General references to bad temper</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov14:17\">PRO 14:17</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt5:22\">MAT 5:22</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps37:8\">PSA 37:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov19:11\">PRO 19:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eccl7:8-Eccl7:9\">ECC 7:8–7:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal5:19-Gal5:20\">GAL 5:19–5:20</a></p>\n<h2>People who lost their temper</h2>\n<h3>Cain</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen4:5\">GEN 4:5</a></strong></p>\n<h3>King Saul</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam20:30\">1SA 20:30</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam18:8\">1SA 18:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam19:9-1Sam19:10\">1SA 19:9–19:10</a></p>\n<h3>Nabal</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam25:14-1Sam25:17\">1SA 25:14–25:17</a></strong></p>\n<h3>Naaman</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs5:11-2Kgs5:12\">2KI 5:11–5:12</a></strong></p>\n<h3>The people in the synagogue at Nazareth</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke4:28-Luke4:29\">LUK 4:28–4:29</a></strong></p>\n<h3>The Pharisees</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke6:11\">LUK 6:11</a></strong></p>\n<h3>The people of Ephesus</h3>\n<p><em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts19:28-Acts19:29\">ACT 19:28–19:29</a></p>\n<h3>Others</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs21:4\">1KI 21:4</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr16:10\">2CH 16:10</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Esth3:5\">EST 3:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Esth3:6\">EST 3:6</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan3:19\">DAN 3:19</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Amos1:11\">AMO 1:11</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts7:57-Acts7:58\">ACT 7:57–7:58</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts22:22-Acts22:23\">ACT 22:22–22:23</a></p>\n<h2>Christians must do all they can to control their temper</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov22:24-Prov22:25\">PRO 22:24–22:25</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph4:26-Eph4:27\">EPH 4:26–4:27</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil4:8\">PHP 4:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas1:19-Jas1:20\">JAS 1:19–1:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet1:13\">1PE 1:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Pet1:5-2Pet1:7\">2PE 1:5–1:7</a></p>\n<h2>God enables Christians to control their temper</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal5:16-Gal5:18\">GAL 5:16–5:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal5:22-Gal5:23\">GAL 5:22–5:23</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil2:12-Phil2:13\">PHP 2:12–2:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim1:7\">2TI 1:7</a></p>",
